Mac:<br><br>
We all hurt, bleed, and fear in the same way. To me, you are just another fellow human with a common bond through the Vietnam Experience. I served with the Big Red One, myself. I, too, have a share in PTSD, the gift that keeps on giving. I still have unresolved pain and feelings about the label of &quot;baby killer&quot; and acts of verbal abuse, discrimination, and being spat upon. That stuff still tears me up inside. It will always. <br><br>
I know it hurts to talk about these things. &quot;Riding in the back of the bus&quot; is a personal experience through which I connect and empathize with fellow Nam Vets and anyone else so afflicted.<br><br>
Speak your mind, brother. I will listen.<br><br>
Welcome home!<br><br>
Peace.<br><br>
Art 
